      Real American style

      One of the better meals we have had in Portugal. Assisted by a waiter, in English, I ordered steak and chips and the wife pizza. We were served garlic bread as a starter and then our orders arrived. The pizza was one of the best...she had ever eaten, my steak was fine. Most enjoyable.More

      Classic diner joint

      Good for kids and cool throwback ambiance. The staff are pleasant and the food passable. The burger was a little overcooked despite claiming to be of premium Azores beef. The restaurant is very family friendly and prices reasonable.

      Date of visit: March 2020

      badmintontim
      2,753 reviews
      Reviewed November 17, 2019 via mobile
      Open till late and helpful staff

      We went here very late and even then the staff were very helpful and told us when the kitchen was closing and that we could have dessert after that if we wished. The food was as expected although they had run out of rice when...we ordered (it was late). The portobello mushroom with the spinach didn’t work for me as it gave it a taste I personally wasn’t keen on. The vegetables were overcooked and I like them al- dente but it appears that to overcook them is the Portuguese way as we had this elsewhere too. Toilets were outside the restaurant in a very poor condition - unsafe toilet seat, not clean etc. This part of the restaurant service (as all eateries should have toilets and somewhere to wash ones hands) needs urgent attention in my opinion. There wasn’t even sufficient soap to wash ones hands - and then go into a food establishment - this is supposed to be Europe!! It’s a shame that these ‘facilities’ or lack of, let the place down as the food was good as was the general service.More

      Reviewed March 23, 2019 via mobile
      Great American style diner

      This place is fun! It’s styled on an American Diner and is very authentic. The food is as you would expect and is cheap. I ordered a basic burger with fries and a strawberry shake. Both were excellent, although the burger was pink in the...middle, I think this is the case with all burgers in Lisbon since it was the same in my hotel. It was very busy and there was a queue for tables as I left but the staff coped well and I was not left waiting long. It’s difficult to find in so much as you need to go into an office block and then up the white marble staircase to get there. Highly recommended.More
